CSS - Cascading Style Sheets

Ways of applying CSS to a page:-
- Inline (through style attribute)
    style - global as well as core attribute
            style="background-color: blue ; color : white;"

- Internal (in the same page using <style> tag inside the head tag (prefered))
    selectors{
        propertyName: value;
        propertyName1 : value1;
    }

- External (using external file using <link> tag)


Priority -> internal < inline ; internal-external -> depends, closer one to the body gets executed

!important -> we use it to give internal a higher priority than inline

frameworks of css - react strap, bootstrap, foundation

Always keep style related things in head

If we have to apply multiple css files in one html doc, instead of writing <link> multiple time, we use
@import url() to import other css files in one file and then give this one in the html doc

