CSS Units

- Types of CSS Units
1. Absolute Units (Fixed)  -> Fixed in size → do not depend on screen or parent
        px → Pixels (most common)
        cm, mm, in → physical units (rare)
        pt, pc → used in print

2. Relative Units (Flexible / Responsive) -> Flexible → depend on parent element or screen size
        (A) Percentage % Relative to parent element
        (B) em Relative to parent font-size
            Can compound (nested effect)
            rem ✅
            Relative to root (html) font-size   
            More predictable than em


CSS Box Model (Short Summary):

Every HTML element is treated as a rectangular box made of 4 layers:

Content
The actual text/image inside the element.

Padding
Space between content and border.
Increases inner spacing.

Border
Surrounds padding and content.
Can have width, style, and color.

Margin
Space outside the border.
Controls distance between elements.

Important:
Total size = content + padding + border + margin

